label: Smalltown Supersound
description:
Hermione Frank joins the Smalltown Supersound family for her most confounding and satisfying set to date: unfurling four hypnotic long-form experimental workouts that drift thru heat-haze dub, freeform jazz, ambient electronix, tight club bumps and beachy neo-nu age wetness. RIYL Donato Dozzy, Huerco S., Batu, CCL or Laurel Halo.

label: Smalltown Supersound
description:
Carmen Villain turns out a career best with her fourth album, a confidently conspicuous co-mingling of dub, fourth world jazz, ambient and kosmische modes. Brilliantly eroded, soft-focus music that's wide-ranging thematically, but completely coherent, landing somewhere between Jon Hassell and Rhythm and Sound.

label: PAN
description:
The most satisfying PAN full-length this year comes from the French duo of cloud rap innovator Lala Ac& and Low Jack, who meets her maple-sweet lullabies and rhymes with speaker burning low-end electricity that sounds like Pan Sonic or Andy Stott rewiring Metro Boomin. Huge recommendation.

label: Hakuna Kulala
description:
Another astonishing debut from Uganda's Hakuna Kulala imprint, 'Raw Space' introduces sonic hypnotist Authentically Plastic, who breaks open East African polyrhythms while nodding to nu-surrealist moves from Dean Blunt, Speaker Music, Nazar and Hieroglyphic Being.
